725239f-a.title: Queens: 35th Avenue - Farrington Street
725239f-a.text:
35th Avenue, at (right), and adjoining the N. W. corner
of Farrington Street. On the left, adjoining the corner,is
Flush'ng Lodge 1468, Loyal Order of Moose. The corner mansion
was known as "The Inn" in 1929. The two buildings comprised
the Kyle Institute in 19O9. The mansion was owned by G. Hicks
in 1891.
P. L. Sperr  April 8, 1927
